heile’ Natur: eine bislang nicht angemessen gewürdigte geistige Dimension des Ökoproblems!  aThe subject of this book is technology’s global domination. It addresses various issues, including technical rationality, artificial intelligence, and watershed historical moments – as well as unintended knock-on effects, such as when technical liberation morphs into structural constraint. Ultimately, it suggests a compelling need for a “post-classical” ethics in response to mass technology.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 4aGlobalisierungsprinzip. 4aMassentechnisierung. 4aPost-klassische Ethik. 7aPHILOSOPHY / History & Surveys / Modern.2bisacsh  aMass technology.  aglobalization.  apost-classical ethics.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2020 Part 1z978311069627108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Philosophy 2020z9783110704648oZDB-23-DPH0 cEPUBz97831106214880 cprintz978311062142640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311062369740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110623697423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110623697/original  a978-3-11-069627-1  DG Plus DeG Package 2020 Part 1b2020  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGGb2020  aZDB-23-DPHb2020